<paragraph id="8BBFB727FFDE9618F50FFED1FBE8FE17" blockId="4.[264,1323,284,790]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Abdomen. Dark brown. Sternite 
<number id="3DC8A500FFDE9618F6F4FED1FD4CFEA7" box="[707,722,284,310]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="9.0">9</number>
with slender halves (
<figureCitation id="133BABA2FFDE9618F7E1FED1FBBCFEA7" box="[982,1058,284,310]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="3.[264,382,1773,1797]" captionTargetBox="[300,1286,563,1738]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[298,1288,556,1747]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Brachypogon (Isohelea) borkenti, n. sp. 1 – 5. female; 6. male. 1. flagellum; 2. maxillary palpus; 3. wing; 4. sternite 9; 5. spermathecae; 6. genitalia. Scale bars = 0.05 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/157313/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Fig. 
<number id="3DC8A500FFDE9618F027FED1FBBCFEA7" box="[1040,1058,284,310]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
); sternite 
<number id="3DC8A500FFDE9618F0ACFED1FB26FEA7" box="[1179,1208,284,310]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="10.0">10</number>
with one pair large setae. Two ovoid, subequal­sized, partially collapsed spermatheca with short, narrow necks (
<figureCitation id="133BABA2FFDE9618F582FEA1FE62FE17" box="[437,508,364,390]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="3.[264,382,1773,1797]" captionTargetBox="[300,1286,563,1738]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[298,1288,556,1747]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Brachypogon (Isohelea) borkenti, n. sp. 1 – 5. female; 6. male. 1. flagellum; 2. maxillary palpus; 3. wing; 4. sternite 9; 5. spermathecae; 6. genitalia. Scale bars = 0.05 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/157313/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Fig. 
<number id="3DC8A500FFDE9618F5DBFEA1FE62FE17" box="[492,508,364,390]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
), measuring 
<number id="3DC8A500FFDE9618F6A2FEA1FD49FE17" box="[661,727,364,390]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="0.075">0.075</number>
by 
<quantity id="4CF81AC2FFDE9618F734FEA1FCE0FE17" box="[771,894,364,390]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.2" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" unit="mm" value="0.052">0.052 mm</quantity>
, 
<number id="3DC8A500FFDE9618F7BEFEA1FC55FE17" box="[905,971,364,390]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="0.066">0.066</number>
by 
<quantity id="4CF81AC2FFDE9618F7C0FEA1FBEDFE17" box="[1015,1139,364,390]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.8" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" unit="mm" value="0.048">0.048 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBFB727FFDE9618F50FFE59FCB1FC87" blockId="4.[264,1323,284,790]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Male. As for female, with usual sexual differences. Lengths of flagellomeres in proportion of 
<date id="FFBE91E7FFDE9618F5B8FE71FDBCFE47" box="[399,546,444,470]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1927-12-16" valueMax="1927-12-13" valueMin="1927-12-16">
<number id="3DC8A500FFDE9618F5B8FE71FE31FE47" box="[399,431,444,470]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="27.0">27</number>
­ 
<number id="3DC8A500FFDE9618F58FFE71FE48FE47" box="[440,470,444,470]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="16.0">16</number>
­ 
<number id="3DC8A500FFDE9618F5E8FE71FE62FE47" box="[479,508,444,470]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="13.0">13</number>
­ 
<number id="3DC8A500FFDE9618F633FE71FDBCFE47" box="[516,546,444,470]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="12.0">12</number>
</date>
­ 
<date id="FFBE91E7FFDE9618F61CFE71FD23FE47" box="[555,701,444,470]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1914-12-12" valueMax="1914-12-14" valueMin="1914-12-12">
<number id="3DC8A500FFDE9618F61CFE71FDD7FE47" box="[555,585,444,470]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="12.0">12</number>
­ 
<number id="3DC8A500FFDE9618F666FE71FD08FE47" box="[593,662,444,470]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="13.0" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="12.0">12­14</number>
­ 
<number id="3DC8A500FFDE9618F6A8FE71FD23FE47" box="[671,701,444,470]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="14.0">14</number>
</date>
­ 
<number id="3DC8A500FFDE9618F6F2FE71FC97FE47" box="[709,777,444,470]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="14.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="14.0">14­15</number>
­ 
<number id="3DC8A500FFDE9618F725FE71FCAAFE47" box="[786,820,444,470]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="40.0">40</number>
­ 
<number id="3DC8A500FFDE9618F70BFE71FC1BFE47" box="[828,901,444,470]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="33.5" valueMax="37.0" valueMin="30.0">30­37</number>
. Wing length 1.00 mm; costal ratio 
<number id="3DC8A500FFDE9618F53FFE29FEA1FE6F" box="[264,319,484,510]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="0.52">0.52</number>
. Genitalia (
<figureCitation id="133BABA2FFDE9618F5FFFE29FD8DFE6F" box="[456,531,484,510]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="3.[264,382,1773,1797]" captionTargetBox="[300,1286,563,1738]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[298,1288,556,1747]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Brachypogon (Isohelea) borkenti, n. sp. 1 – 5. female; 6. male. 1. flagellum; 2. maxillary palpus; 3. wing; 4. sternite 9; 5. spermathecae; 6. genitalia. Scale bars = 0.05 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/157313/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Fig. 
<number id="3DC8A500FFDE9618F636FE29FD8DFE6F" box="[513,531,484,510]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
): Tergite 
<number id="3DC8A500FFDE9618F6B2FE29FD0AFE6F" box="[645,660,484,510]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="9.0">9</number>
quadrate, as long as breadth, posterior margin truncate; posterior projection heptagonal with heavily sclerotized margins, apicolateral processes slender, moderately long, each with one apical seta, cercus short; sternite 
<number id="3DC8A500FFDE9618F046FDF9FB1EFDDF" box="[1137,1152,564,590]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="9.0">9</number>
<number id="3DC8A500FFDE9618F0BFFDF9FB33FDDF" box="[1160,1197,564,590]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="0.2">0.2</number>
as long as wide, posterior margin irregular. Gonocoxite stout, without mesobasal lobe; gonostylus 
<number id="3DC8A500FFDE9618F53FFD49FEA5FD0F" box="[264,315,644,670]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="0.75">0.75</number>
as long as gonocoxite, nearly straight, tip pointed. Parameres separated, each half represented by two heavily sclerotized, narrowly pointed recurved sclerites, one directed anteriorly, other bifid, directed posteriorly. Aedeagus stout; basal arms short, recurved; basal arch very low, irregular; apex not visible.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
