<subSubSection id="C31AE4ACFFDE9618F53FFB11FBB8FAD7" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BBFB727FFDE9618F53FFB11FE1BFB64" blockId="4.[264,1323,1244,1350]" box="[264,389,1244,1269]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis id="B9746B35FFDE9618F53FFB11FE1BFB64" box="[264,389,1244,1269]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Etymology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBFB727FFDE9618F50FFAC9FBB8FAD7" blockId="4.[264,1323,1244,1350]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
The species is named after our colleague and good friend, Dr. Art Borkent, in recognition of his superb contributions on systematics of 
<taxonomicName id="4C00CCA4FFDE9618F761FAE1FBBCFAD7" box="[854,1058,1324,1350]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Ceratopogonidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
